HEADWORD: Disloign
<hw>Dis*loign"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>desloignier</ets>. See <er>Eloign</er>.]</ety> <def>To put at a
distance; to remove.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Low-looking dales, <qex>disloigned</qex> from common gaze.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

